# @opentelemetry/exporter-prometheus + @opentelemetry/sdk-node Prometheus HTTP listener crash
# (GHSA-q7rr-3cgh-j5r3; affects exporter-prometheus shipped with sdk-node 0.x)
# Fixed upstream in exporter-prometheus >= 0.220.x, which in turn requires the whole
# OpenTelemetry stack to move past 0.220. The .syncpackrc.json holds sdk-node and
# every paired exporter/instrumentation package pinned at ^0.211.0 across all
# workspaces for compatible runtime semantics; bumping just one package leaves npm
# with duplicate otel installs that syncpack's sameRange highestSemver group rejects.
# Importantly, we never start the Prometheus HTTP scrape endpoint: telemetry leaves
# every workspace via OTLP HTTP exporters to our collector, not via the Prometheus
# pull endpoint. The malformed-request DoS lives only inside the HTTP listener code
# path that we do not enable, so the advisory is not reachable from any deployed
# surface at runtime.
# BLOCKER: transitive via pinned @opentelemetry/sdk-node ^0.211.0; the vulnerable Prometheus HTTP listener is never started in our config (OTLP-only egress), so the malformed-request DoS is structurally unreachable; revisit when the syncpack OpenTelemetry pin advances past 0.220
